Actor Sean Andrew Kibaki and his brother Kibaki Jnr are remembering their grandmother Lucy Kibaki, four years after she died. Lucy Muthoni Kibaki was the wife of former President Mwai Kibaki and was the First Lady from 2002 to 2013. She died on April 26, 2016, in South Kensington, London, United Kingdom. On their social media pages, the two grandchildren paid their tributes. Sean Andrew shared a photo of the late former first lady and wrote, “Rest with the angels forever.” Kibaki Jnr, on the other hand, wrote, “Always on my mind, forever in my heart.” Sean Andrew caught the attention of many during the funeral of his grandmother. Since then, he has been a public figure who is now an influencer.